DISCUSSION
We found that young and middle-age women with a recent MI had a doubling of the odds of developing MSIMI compared with men, and they also showed a similar increase in ischemia induced by conventional stress. This finding was observed despite the fact that women had less obstructive CAD than men. Of several hemodynamic and vascular measures, a lower PAT ratio, indicator of peripheral vasoconstriction with mental stress, and a lower resting RHI, a marker of baseline mi-

